				h1.articleheading who is DEADEYE?
				p.articletext Raised in a warzone, the sinister sniper DEADEYE grew up day and night with a gun in her hand. After escaping from her forced conscription alongside her estranged sister, DEADEYE kept that same gun on her waist for safety. Since that day, her gun has made her rich, powerful and feared. 

				p.articletext DEADEYE is on a brutal sharpshooter contracted with Knox's Villain Underground. As a professional assassin, DEADEYE has quickly gained a reputation as a cold-blooded killer. Despite an everpresent disgust with her teammates, DEADEYE has proven to be a dangerous and loyal ally to the Villain Underground. 
		.row.articlerow
			.col-md-12
				h1.articleheading how to play DEADEYE
				p.articletext Handguns. Shotguns. Sniper Rifles. Plastique. The no-nonsense mercenary DEADEYE is resigned to use whatever it takes to get the job done. DEADEYE herself has no natural superpowers, but frequently clashes with both heroes and villains in dangerous shootouts. If you've got the guts to take the safety off, playing as Deadeye offers explosive rewards -  if you can manage to pull the trigger.

				p.articletext DEADEYE is an aggressive combo character that can alternate between attacking your opponent's hand and their life total. DEADEYE's AIM skill allows you to dramatically increase the damage dealt by cards in your deck. When playing as Deadeye, it's not uncommon to play Actions dealing upwards of 8 or 9 damage. DEADEYE's defensive options may be limited, but sometimes the best defense is a good offense.
	
				p.articletext To play DEADEYE, you'll have to embrace being cutthroat. DEADEYE offers a lot of options in terms of player damage and discard strategies, but struggles with surviving into the later turns of the game. Players can include more defensive Crossovers as a way of shoring up this weakness. 

				p.articletext By regularly and aggressively attacking your opponent, Deadeye shines as one of the centerpiece aggro characters of the game. Marked as an EASY character, DEADEYE is a great option for new players. Want to set the pace? Tired of waiting around for slow players? Pick up Deadeye and start firing live rounds.
